00:05:43.320 --> 00:05:50.960
I had the idea of
something similar to what

00:05:50.960 --> 00:05:53.670
President Kennedy and then
President Johnson did.

00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:56.070
In terms of the
social investment,

00:05:56.070 --> 00:05:59.420
the Civil Rights Act.

00:05:59.420 --> 00:06:07.640
And we started to have Congress
pass reforms, approve reforms,

00:06:07.640 --> 00:06:09.600
which were very important.

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:12.530
For example, in the
last eight years

00:06:12.530 --> 00:06:18.560
we made access to our health
system a fundamental right.

00:06:18.560 --> 00:06:22.040
And we now have
universal coverage.

00:06:22.040 --> 00:06:29.570
We made education free for
every boy and girl in Colombia,

00:06:29.570 --> 00:06:32.600
from kindergarten
to the 11th grade.

00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:37.130
And we increased, substantially,
the access to higher education.

00:06:37.130 --> 00:06:42.740
And for the first time, we put
education on top of our budget.

00:06:42.740 --> 00:06:48.380
Usually, for the last 100
years, defense and security

00:06:48.380 --> 00:06:50.110
were the number one.

00:06:50.110 --> 00:06:51.180
Well, we changed that.

00:06:51.180 --> 00:06:54.050
We put education as number one.

00:06:54.050 --> 00:07:00.560
We made a very ambitious
program for modernizing

00:07:00.560 --> 00:07:03.770
our infrastructure.

00:07:03.770 --> 00:07:09.440
And we have, right now,
in place a real revolution

00:07:09.440 --> 00:07:12.395
in terms of modernizing
our highways, our ports.

00:07:15.750 --> 00:07:18.200
Last time we went to
Bogota, you arrived

00:07:18.200 --> 00:07:20.840
to the airport, which is
the most modern airport

00:07:20.840 --> 00:07:22.610
in the whole of Latin America.

00:07:22.610 --> 00:07:24.560
Number one in cargo.

00:07:24.560 --> 00:07:31.940
Number three in passengers
after Mexico and Sao Paolo.

00:07:31.940 --> 00:07:37.400
And we put in
place some programs

00:07:37.400 --> 00:07:43.430
that allowed us to
improve substantially,

00:07:43.430 --> 00:07:44.810
our social indicators.

00:07:44.810 --> 00:07:51.270
For example, our
fight against poverty.

00:07:51.270 --> 00:07:54.310
And we innovated there.

00:07:54.310 --> 00:08:01.660
I had a professor in
Harvard who won the Nobel

00:08:01.660 --> 00:08:03.700
Prize in economics.

00:08:03.700 --> 00:08:07.480
He comes from
India, Amartya Sen,

00:08:07.480 --> 00:08:14.390
who had a very different
idea of measuring progress,

00:08:14.390 --> 00:08:15.620
measuring prosperity.

00:08:18.140 --> 00:08:23.720
Very similar-- I brought
a part of his speech--

00:08:23.720 --> 00:08:28.220
very similar to what Robert
Kennedy had at that time.

00:08:28.220 --> 00:08:36.280
I went to the University
of Kansas in 1969.

00:08:36.280 --> 00:08:42.700
In March of 1968, Robert Kennedy
went to University of Kansas.

00:08:42.700 --> 00:08:45.280
And I have here,
part of his speech.

00:08:47.890 --> 00:08:52.150
I want to read it to you,
because it's very inspiring.

00:08:52.150 --> 00:08:57.580
He said, even if we act
to erase material poverty,

00:08:57.580 --> 00:09:01.370
there is another greater task.

00:09:01.370 --> 00:09:05.950
It is to confront poverty
of satisfaction, purpose,

00:09:05.950 --> 00:09:09.700
and dignity that
afflicts us all.

00:09:09.700 --> 00:09:13.180
Too much for too long, we
seem to have surrendered

00:09:13.180 --> 00:09:14.710
personal excellence
and community

00:09:14.710 --> 00:09:20.770
values in the mere accumulation
of material things.

00:09:20.770 --> 00:09:25.480
Our gross national product now
is over $800 billion a year.

00:09:25.480 --> 00:09:27.610
But that gross
national product--

00:09:27.610 --> 00:09:31.670
if we judge the United
States of America by that--

00:09:31.670 --> 00:09:35.180
that gross national product
counts air pollution

00:09:35.180 --> 00:09:36.680
and cigarette advertising.

00:09:36.680 --> 00:09:40.730
And ambulances to clear
our highways of carnage.

00:09:40.730 --> 00:09:44.060
It counts special
locks for our doors.

00:09:44.060 --> 00:09:46.580
And the jails for the
people who break them.

00:09:46.580 --> 00:09:49.940
It counts the destruction
of the Redwood.

00:09:49.940 --> 00:09:54.830
And the loss of our natural
wonder in chaotic sprawl.

00:09:54.830 --> 00:09:56.330
It counts napalm.

00:09:56.330 --> 00:09:59.360
And counts nuclear
warheads in armored cars

00:09:59.360 --> 00:10:02.270
for the police to fight
the riots in our cities.

00:10:02.270 --> 00:10:07.040
It counts Whitman's
rifle and Speck's knife.

00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:10.670
And the television programs
which glorify violence in order

00:10:10.670 --> 00:10:13.610
to sell toys to our children.

00:10:13.610 --> 00:10:16.940
Yet, the gross national
product does not

00:10:16.940 --> 00:10:21.270
allow for the health
of our children,

00:10:21.270 --> 00:10:27.650
the quality of their education
or the joy of their play.

00:10:27.650 --> 00:10:30.650
It does not include the
beauty of our poetry.

00:10:30.650 --> 00:10:32.960
Or the strength
of our marriages.

00:10:32.960 --> 00:10:37.580
The intelligence of our
public debate or the integrity

00:10:37.580 --> 00:10:40.370
of our public officials.

00:10:40.370 --> 00:10:45.590
It measures neither our
whit nor our courage.

00:10:45.590 --> 00:10:49.070
Neither our wisdom
nor our learning.

00:10:49.070 --> 00:10:53.580
Neither our compassion nor
our devotion to our country.

00:10:53.580 --> 00:10:58.100
It measures everything
in short, except that

00:10:58.100 --> 00:11:02.360
which makes life worthwhile.

00:11:02.360 --> 00:11:06.650
And it can tell us everything
about America except why we are

00:11:06.650 --> 00:11:08.930
proud that we are Americans.

00:11:11.930 --> 00:11:18.440
That was very similar of what
Professor Sen was teaching.

00:11:18.440 --> 00:11:19.900
And so I called him.

00:11:19.900 --> 00:11:22.580
And I said,
professor Sen, I want

00:11:22.580 --> 00:11:26.730
to apply your theory
in my country.

00:11:26.730 --> 00:11:29.960
And he said, OK, come to Oxford.

00:11:29.960 --> 00:11:33.530
I took the presidential
plane and flew to Oxford.

00:11:33.530 --> 00:11:39.590
And he set up a
group of his advisors

00:11:39.590 --> 00:11:41.810
and his people who
worked with him.

00:11:41.810 --> 00:11:44.270
Went back to Columbia,
and we established

00:11:44.270 --> 00:11:49.610
something called a
multidimensional poverty index.

00:11:49.610 --> 00:11:53.060
And we approved
laws in Congress.

00:11:53.060 --> 00:11:54.020
And made reforms.

00:11:54.020 --> 00:11:55.940
And created the institutions.

00:11:55.940 --> 00:11:58.910
And started fighting
poverty, measuring

00:11:58.910 --> 00:12:05.150
these type of basic
necessities that people

00:12:05.150 --> 00:12:07.570
needed to be satisfied.

00:12:07.570 --> 00:12:14.060
And that allowed us to
invest our social expenditure

00:12:14.060 --> 00:12:18.860
with a much higher
return socially.

00:12:18.860 --> 00:12:21.830
And that's why Colombia,
in relative terms,

00:12:21.830 --> 00:12:23.990
had brought down poverty.

00:12:23.990 --> 00:12:25.430
And extreme poverty.

00:12:25.430 --> 00:12:27.620
And inequality,
which is a problem

00:12:27.620 --> 00:12:32.330
for all of Latin America,
more than other countries

00:12:32.330 --> 00:12:33.720
in our region.

00:12:33.720 --> 00:12:39.740
So in all of this, we have
tried to do with what we call,

00:12:39.740 --> 00:12:41.990
fiscal responsibility.

00:12:41.990 --> 00:12:45.320
You know better
than me and anybody

00:12:45.320 --> 00:12:47.660
because your
economics professor,

00:12:47.660 --> 00:12:51.680
how to maintain the
confidence in your economy.

00:12:51.680 --> 00:12:55.250
And maintain the
confidence of investors.

00:12:55.250 --> 00:12:57.800
In order to be
able to grow, it's

00:12:57.800 --> 00:12:59.600
one of the necessary conditions.

00:12:59.600 --> 00:13:09.080
So, to summarize, Colombia
has had a responsible

00:13:09.080 --> 00:13:11.040
macroeconomic policy.

00:13:11.040 --> 00:13:14.840
And at the same time, a very
aggressive social policy.

00:13:14.840 --> 00:13:21.590
That has allowed us to perform
much better than Venezuela.

00:13:21.590 --> 00:13:24.800
I will tell you an anecdote,
which comes to the point

00:13:24.800 --> 00:13:26.960
that you were asking.

